WEBVTT

00:02.753 --> 00:05.755
NARRATOR: In the future,
a computer program called Skynet...

00:05.923 --> 00:08.257
...will declare war on the human race.

00:09.593 --> 00:12.762
Machines have traveled back in time,
taking human form...

00:12.930 --> 00:17.433
...to terminate John Connor,
the future leader of the Resistance.

00:18.936 --> 00:23.231
Sarah Connor,
John's mother, teacher and protector.

00:24.024 --> 00:28.611
Cameron, a Terminator reprogrammed
to defend them at all costs.

00:29.279 --> 00:34.117
Derek Reese, John's uncle, and a
commanding officer with the Resistance.

00:34.284 --> 00:38.287
Together, they fight to stop
Skynet from ever being created.

00:38.455 --> 00:41.290
The battle for our tomorrow starts today.

00:46.505 --> 00:49.382
ANNOUNCER: Previously on
Terminator: The Sarah Connor Chronicles:

00:49.550 --> 00:51.259
Do we have a John Reese?

00:55.222 --> 00:57.140
[GRUNTING]

00:58.058 --> 00:59.517
Come with me if you wanna live.

00:59.685 --> 01:02.145
I'm not who they think I am,
some messiah.

01:02.312 --> 01:05.148
-You've gotta stop it. Please.
SARAH: I'll stop it.

01:05.315 --> 01:07.316
You wanna stop Skynet? This is the way.

01:08.861 --> 01:11.112
CAMERON:
He came through. He knows we're here.

01:11.613 --> 01:14.824
We're programmed to repair ourselves.
We're programmed to blend in.

01:14.992 --> 01:16.033
[GRUNTS]

01:16.201 --> 01:19.162
SARAH: There are other people he sent back.
CAMERON: Resistance fighters.

01:19.329 --> 01:21.706
-You don't even know who he is.
-He's your uncle.

01:21.874 --> 01:23.583
The machines gotta go.

01:23.751 --> 01:27.837
DEREK: Don't think you can train them like
a pet. It'll be the last thing you think.

01:28.005 --> 01:31.382
ELLISON: Your fiancÃ©e, Sarah Connor,
killed a man. She believes, in the future...

01:31.550 --> 01:34.635
...he'll invent a computer system
that declares war on the world.

01:34.803 --> 01:38.723
ANDY: My Turk plays chess at a level
that could defeat every human player...

01:38.891 --> 01:42.185
-...that has lived or ever will live.
-I might just blow up the world.

01:42.352 --> 01:45.104
Sarkissian called me.
He'll meet about selling The Turk.

01:46.106 --> 01:48.191
-Guy that Derek killed.
-Sarkissian.

01:48.358 --> 01:50.485
I don't think that was Sarkissian.

01:51.528 --> 01:54.447
If you die, they win.

08:14.744 --> 08:16.745
[SIREN WAILING]

08:16.913 --> 08:18.914
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER RADIO]

08:27.841 --> 08:31.594
Agent Ellison? Can I borrow you?

08:34.431 --> 08:37.933
Pulled him from the apartment.
That's your guy, right? The shooter?

08:39.144 --> 08:40.895
Yeah, that's him.

08:41.062 --> 08:44.815
NORGAARD: How does a mope like that
take out 20 of our HRT?

08:46.276 --> 08:48.944
SAC wants you back home
for a full incident report.

08:49.279 --> 08:50.279
Need a ride?

08:50.864 --> 08:53.616
I can get a junior agent
to drive your car. Come on.

08:56.995 --> 09:00.289
They're gonna believe a mope like this
took out 20 of your HRT?

09:00.457 --> 09:04.460
They gonna believe a machine
from the future stole his identity and did it?

09:05.462 --> 09:10.549
They gotta believe. This has to end here.

09:10.967 --> 09:14.678
Sorry you gotta take the blame for it.
It's not your fault.

09:16.473 --> 09:18.682
Just bad luck.

09:22.312 --> 09:23.479
Are you all right?

09:25.106 --> 09:26.273
John, are you all right?

09:27.484 --> 09:28.776
You answer me!

09:29.819 --> 09:31.028
Mom!

09:31.238 --> 09:33.239
[CAR HORN HONKING]

09:37.994 --> 09:40.287
Can you move? Are you hurt?
You're bleeding.

09:40.455 --> 09:42.581
-I'm fine. Are you all right?
-It's just my shoulder.

09:42.749 --> 09:44.166
[PEOPLE SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY]

09:44.334 --> 09:45.668
We gotta go.

09:46.169 --> 09:47.503
[JOHN GRUNTING]

09:49.005 --> 09:51.131
-Can you walk?
-Yeah.

09:51.299 --> 09:52.591
Good, because we gotta run.

09:52.759 --> 09:54.009
-Hey! Hey!
-Hey!

09:54.177 --> 09:56.136
MAN:
Come back here!

10:16.950 --> 10:19.535
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]: Fire and EMT
personnel, advised to stand by.

10:19.703 --> 10:22.746
Fire has destroyed a home
at 204 Laurel Avenue.

10:22.914 --> 10:24.915
Number of dead or injured is unknown.

10:30.630 --> 10:32.631
[MEN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

10:32.841 --> 10:35.592
MAN 1: The gas line is behind
that bearing wall through there.

10:37.554 --> 10:39.179
Go ahead, pull it.

10:42.976 --> 10:45.686
MAN 2: Bring it up.
MAN 1: He's working on the left side.

11:04.289 --> 11:07.750
-Hey. These the only two DOA?
-That's it.

11:07.917 --> 11:10.502
-You check the whole house?
-House is clear.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.351
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCLTY]

11:36.321 --> 11:38.989
What the hell is going on here?
Where is she?

11:39.532 --> 11:42.618
Hell if I know.
Long gone, if I know her.

11:43.495 --> 11:46.372
-Who's out there under those sheets?
-We were doing a deal.

11:46.539 --> 11:52.127
It went bad. We stole this.
Guess they came back for it.

11:52.545 --> 11:56.298
-What's on it?
-Oh, records, names, transactions.

11:56.466 --> 11:57.800
I don't know.

11:57.967 --> 12:00.052
We thought we could use it
to find something.

12:00.261 --> 12:04.264
-What are you looking for?
-It's a piece of tech. It's called The Turk.

12:06.518 --> 12:08.977
-It's another computer. It's a program.
-What's it do?

12:09.145 --> 12:12.481
Right now? Plays a mean game of chess.
Couple years?

12:12.649 --> 12:15.818
It's gonna get really pissed off.
Blow up the world.

12:16.694 --> 12:17.861
WOMAN [OVER RADIO]:
Units requested.

12:18.029 --> 12:19.988
Possible stolen vehicle
involved in accident.

12:20.156 --> 12:23.534
Suspect fled scene, injuries unknown.

12:24.536 --> 12:27.371
-She could be anywhere.
-That's right, she could be anywhere.

12:27.539 --> 12:31.500
Or she could be right there.
Maybe with your chess program.

12:35.797 --> 12:38.841
The identification of these two victims
hasn't yet been released...

12:39.008 --> 12:42.719
...and it's unclear how they're connected
to this or the car explosion nearby.

12:43.179 --> 12:44.179
WOMAN:
Mr. Walsh?

12:44.848 --> 12:46.682
-Ma'am.
-Do you have it?

12:46.933 --> 12:50.018
I do, ma'am.
It's a modest little mouse, if I may say.

12:50.186 --> 12:52.479
It's not much to look at for 300,000.

12:52.647 --> 12:54.565
Better be able to checkmate
Bobby Fischer.

12:54.732 --> 12:56.817
Not for you to judge, Mr. Walsh.

12:56.985 --> 12:59.403
-The last you'll hear of it from me.
-When will I see you?

12:59.571 --> 13:01.780
I thought I'd tour the sights
with it for a bit.

13:01.948 --> 13:04.992
-Make sure I was clean.
WOMAN: That seems prudent.

13:05.160 --> 13:08.036
-An hour, then?
-An hour.

13:08.413 --> 13:13.709
And, Mr. Walsh? Bobby Fischer's dead.

13:20.341 --> 13:21.592
[PHONE BEEPS]

13:21.759 --> 13:22.926
WOMAN [OVER SPEAKERPHONE]:
Ma'am?

13:23.094 --> 13:25.095
Call a meeting
of the department heads for tonight.

13:25.263 --> 13:30.517
Tonight? But, Miss Weaver, Justin Tuck
is in Palm Springs for a long weekend.

13:31.227 --> 13:34.146
-I'll get him back.
-Thank you.

14:04.010 --> 14:06.011
[STAPLE GUN CLICKING]

14:11.267 --> 14:13.268
[SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

14:15.605 --> 14:17.940
Witness saw a woman and a boy
get out of the car...

14:18.107 --> 14:19.900
...and move off to the south.

14:20.068 --> 14:22.486
-Are they hurt?
-Either way, they're moving.

14:32.038 --> 14:33.163
[GRUNTS]

14:35.792 --> 14:39.253
I'm okay. I'm okay.
It's just bruised. Let's go.

14:39.420 --> 14:42.965
-It could be broken.
-How's your leg?

14:43.132 --> 14:46.635
Is your head still bleeding?
Gotta get off the street.

14:46.803 --> 14:48.929
We need to find a safe place.

15:15.665 --> 15:18.000
[PRIEST SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

15:29.429 --> 15:31.179
Has there been an accident?

15:33.850 --> 15:36.184
[BOTH SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

15:45.320 --> 15:47.029
We need sanctuary.

15:49.032 --> 15:51.742
Can I ask for that? Please?

15:52.619 --> 15:55.245
We need somewhere to hide. Now.

15:58.541 --> 16:02.628
Yes. Of course. Come with me.

16:04.380 --> 16:05.464
And they should leave.

16:07.300 --> 16:09.801
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:16.184 --> 16:17.351
Come on.

16:17.518 --> 16:19.519
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

16:20.188 --> 16:23.231
-So, what are you gonna do?
-Do?

16:23.399 --> 16:27.527
Join the team? Think she's gonna
go with you or let you take care of her?

16:27.695 --> 16:31.031
Because that's not gonna happen.
She left you at the altar for a reason.

16:31.199 --> 16:33.825
-That's not what I want.
-Really?

16:33.993 --> 16:35.994
-Yeah, I'm married.
-So you say.

16:36.162 --> 16:39.122
-I love my wife.
-So you say.

16:39.415 --> 16:41.583
Look, I just wanna know they're okay.
Got it?

16:41.751 --> 16:44.419
-What if they're not?
-Then I'll make them okay.

16:44.587 --> 16:46.588
Like I did for you.

16:54.639 --> 16:56.640
[CHATTERING]

17:19.288 --> 17:22.416
Your money will be deposited
in the account within 30 minutes.

17:22.709 --> 17:26.128
Please, take all the precautions
we discussed.

17:26.295 --> 17:32.467
Of course, ma'am. So much for so little.
Again, don't mind me saying.

17:36.222 --> 17:39.683
They flow from street to street...

17:40.643 --> 17:43.895
...at a particular speed
and in a particular direction.

17:44.313 --> 17:47.107
Walk the block. Wait for the signal.

17:47.275 --> 17:51.319
Cross at the light. Over and over.

17:51.654 --> 17:54.990
So orderly. All day, I can watch them...

17:55.158 --> 17:59.536
...and know with a great deal of certainty
what they'll do at any given moment.

18:00.329 --> 18:07.169
But they're not orderly, are they?
Up close. Any individual.

18:07.754 --> 18:10.213
Who knows what they're gonna do?

18:11.424 --> 18:13.550
Any one of them might
dash across the street...

18:13.718 --> 18:15.677
...at the wrong time
and get hit by a car.

18:17.263 --> 18:21.850
When you get up close,
we never follow the rules.

18:22.935 --> 18:27.355
You give a computer a series of rules,
and it will follow them...

18:27.523 --> 18:30.442
...till those rules
are superseded by other rules...

18:30.610 --> 18:35.113
...or that computer simply
wears down and quits.

18:35.448 --> 18:38.575
Computers are obedient to a fault.

18:38.868 --> 18:42.078
Do you know what's extremely rare
in the world of computers?

18:42.246 --> 18:47.375
Finding one that'll cross against the light.

18:49.629 --> 18:51.004
Thank you, Mr. Walsh.

18:54.050 --> 18:55.884
Be careful out there.

19:01.349 --> 19:03.350
[MAN SPEAKING IN SPANISH
OVER RADIO]

19:10.817 --> 19:12.526
Are you all right?

19:15.738 --> 19:18.406
-You already asked me that.
-I'm asking you again.

19:18.574 --> 19:20.408
I'm fine.

19:20.743 --> 19:23.245
We need to talk about
what happened back at the house.

19:23.412 --> 19:25.831
-No, we don't.
-Maybe I need to talk about it.

19:25.998 --> 19:30.001
Maybe you do, but I don't,
so let's not. Please.

19:33.005 --> 19:35.215
Then we need to talk about her.

19:35.758 --> 19:39.636
Whatever happened with the explosion,
it's flipped a switch.

19:40.054 --> 19:42.430
She's reverted or something.

19:42.598 --> 19:45.934
-She knows everything.
-I know.

19:46.102 --> 19:49.563
Bank accounts. Contingency plans.
Weapons stash.

19:49.730 --> 19:51.773
-I know.
-How we run, where we'll go.

19:51.941 --> 19:56.778
Who we've been, who we'll be.
She's stronger and faster.

19:56.946 --> 19:58.947
-We have to kill her, John.
-I know!

20:10.209 --> 20:11.793
I know.

20:19.260 --> 20:21.261
FEDERICI:
I just read your incident report.

20:21.429 --> 20:24.598
I wanna thank you
for filling everything out so quickly.

20:24.765 --> 20:27.267
-It's a big help.
-Of course.

20:27.435 --> 20:31.646
So Laszlo.
Did you ever think that he had it in him?

20:31.814 --> 20:35.400
-Out-of-work-actor, a civilian?
-I did not, no.

20:35.568 --> 20:38.486
But he was here before.
Suspect in multiple murders.

20:38.654 --> 20:41.281
-We cleared him.
-You had a change of heart, obviously.

20:41.449 --> 20:44.826
I discovered he was
impersonating an FBI agent.

20:44.994 --> 20:47.704
Yeah. Yeah, I had a change of heart.

20:47.872 --> 20:51.166
Do you have any idea whose bullet
was ultimately responsible...

20:51.334 --> 20:52.500
...for taking his life?

20:52.668 --> 20:53.752
No, I don't.

20:53.920 --> 20:56.838
Do you know who threw
the tear gas into the residence?

20:57.006 --> 20:58.340
-No.
-Do you know who fired...

20:58.507 --> 21:00.675
...into the apartment,
igniting the canisters?

21:01.135 --> 21:02.302
No, I do not.

21:02.470 --> 21:04.429
It's amazing you survived.

21:07.808 --> 21:10.977
-Do you know how you survived?
-No.

21:18.152 --> 21:20.445
You wanna talk to somebody?
You need help?

21:20.613 --> 21:22.447
You want a counselor,
you want a pastor?

21:22.615 --> 21:25.283
-You're divorced. Do you have anybody?
-I'll be all right.

21:25.826 --> 21:28.828
We want you to take six weeks'
paid leave. Special circumstances.

21:28.996 --> 21:31.748
-I don't think that'll be necessary.
-We insist on it.

21:34.502 --> 21:35.669
So....

21:35.836 --> 21:41.591
Under possible penalty of perjury,
as relates to Case File B1987004...

21:41.759 --> 21:45.178
...do you, Agent James Ellison,
today attest that all you've recorded...

21:45.346 --> 21:49.265
...in said case file is accurate and factual
as far as your recollection can warrant?

21:51.394 --> 21:53.853
Yes. I do.

21:58.401 --> 22:00.360
Good luck, agent.

22:32.727 --> 22:34.436
Yes? May I help you?

22:36.605 --> 22:39.274
-I'm looking for my family.
-Your family?

22:39.442 --> 22:40.859
My mother and my brother.

22:41.819 --> 22:44.112
We were in an accident.
I think they're hurt.

22:45.114 --> 22:47.407
There is no one here.

22:47.783 --> 22:50.618
I need to find them. It's life or death.

22:51.412 --> 22:56.374
-Like I said, there is no one here.
-I'm going to look around.

22:58.586 --> 23:00.712
It's life or death.

23:30.159 --> 23:31.451
Now.

23:33.996 --> 23:36.581
-Two minutes.
-I know.

23:40.419 --> 23:43.088
PRIEST: What are you doing?
-Stay away. Please.

23:43.506 --> 23:46.132
I told you to go away.
You have to stay away.

23:47.259 --> 23:48.510
Go!

23:50.429 --> 23:51.513
Seventy seconds.

23:51.680 --> 23:54.766
-I know. The knife isn't sharp enough.
-Well, push harder.

23:55.893 --> 23:58.520
-How much time?
-Fifty-five.

23:59.772 --> 24:02.899
Oh, wait, I see it, I see it, I see it.
Screwdriver, screwdriver.

24:05.653 --> 24:08.154
-Thirty-five.
-It's not the right size.

24:08.322 --> 24:12.200
-Twenty seconds.
-Okay, okay. The knife, the knife.

24:15.996 --> 24:18.873
-Unh. Damn it!
-We can't do this. Come on, John.

24:19.041 --> 24:21.876
She's waking up. She's waking up.

24:36.308 --> 24:38.184
[CAR HORNS HONKING]

24:46.485 --> 24:48.069
SARAH:
Keys.

25:06.922 --> 25:08.590
[TRUCK HORN HONKING]

25:20.603 --> 25:22.187
[MAN GRUNTS THEN
SHOUTS INDISTINCTLY]

26:02.186 --> 26:04.187
[JOHN COUGHING]

26:10.069 --> 26:15.531
Mom.

26:27.086 --> 26:28.544
You have to go, John.

26:30.673 --> 26:32.131
-John.
-What?

26:32.383 --> 26:35.176
Go. Go.

26:36.470 --> 26:37.929
Go.

26:38.806 --> 26:40.181
Go!

26:41.308 --> 27:03.329
[GRUNTING]

27:09.962 --> 27:12.714
-Call to him.
-No.

27:13.882 --> 27:14.924
Call to him.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.974
[SCREAMS]

27:30.316 --> 27:32.775
-You're making this difficult.
-He won't come back!

27:34.987 --> 27:36.863
No, he won't.

28:36.173 --> 28:38.174
[GRUNTING]

28:41.387 --> 28:42.470
[CLATTERING]

29:14.211 --> 29:16.421
[ENGINE RATTLING THEN CLICKS]

29:26.598 --> 29:28.599
[ENGINE SPLUTTERING]

29:37.317 --> 29:39.318
[ENGINE REWING]

30:15.439 --> 30:18.566
John. John. You can't do this.

30:18.734 --> 30:22.195
-You don't know what you're about to do.
-Yes, I do. You're gonna kill me.

30:22.362 --> 30:25.364
No. John, you can't do this.

30:25.532 --> 30:28.826
You're not doing the right thing.
This is not the right thing, John.

30:28.994 --> 30:32.914
Things are good now.
Things are fine now. I ran a test.

30:33.081 --> 30:36.250
Things are good now. I'm fixed now.
You can trust me now.

30:36.418 --> 30:38.669
-Everything's good now.
-What are you waiting for?

30:38.837 --> 30:41.255
She doesn't know. She doesn't.
I'm good now.

30:41.423 --> 30:44.091
I'm good. I ran a test.
Everything's perfect. I'm perfect.

30:44.259 --> 30:46.385
-John!
-I'm sorry for what I did. I'm sorry.

30:46.553 --> 30:49.055
It wasn't me.
You have to understand. It wasn't me.

30:49.223 --> 30:51.974
That wasn't me. You can't
let this happen, John. You can't.

30:52.142 --> 30:56.229
Please, listen to me. Listen to me.
I don't wanna go. Please, John, please.

30:57.189 --> 30:59.357
John, listen to me. I don't wanna go.

30:59.816 --> 31:03.361
Please, John. Please? I'm good now.

31:03.737 --> 31:06.155
Listen to me. I don't wanna go. I'm sorry.

31:06.323 --> 31:09.492
That wasn't me.
I'm fixed now. I ran a test.

31:09.660 --> 31:13.287
-Everything's perfect. You can trust me.
-John Connor.

31:13.455 --> 31:18.125
I love you. I love you. Please.
I love you, John, and you love me.

31:44.695 --> 31:45.903
We should get going soon.

31:46.405 --> 31:49.407
You cut a pretty serious
path of destruction across the city.

31:49.575 --> 31:51.242
Wasn't us.

31:51.952 --> 31:53.286
[GRUNTS]

31:53.620 --> 31:55.246
-Sorry.
-Should've called earlier.

31:55.414 --> 31:58.124
-Maybe we could've helped you avoid those.
-I doubt it.

32:00.669 --> 32:03.671
-How's this?
DEREK: Looks trashed.

32:03.964 --> 32:07.508
So Sarkissian didn't tell you where
he sold The Turk before you killed him.

32:08.510 --> 32:10.052
Wasn't that kind of conversation.

32:14.975 --> 32:16.684
DEREK:
Did he see it all?

32:16.852 --> 32:18.185
He saw it all.

32:20.230 --> 32:21.606
Damn.

32:35.203 --> 32:38.873
Charlie told me that Cromartie
killed about 20 FBI guys today.

32:39.875 --> 32:41.959
He's still out there.

32:42.919 --> 32:44.587
He's here for me.

32:44.755 --> 32:46.255
They're dead because of me.

32:46.423 --> 32:50.384
They're dead because some people
refuse to accept the reality of the situation.

32:50.552 --> 32:52.011
Which is what?

32:52.179 --> 32:55.640
Which is that they carry death with them.

32:56.266 --> 32:58.893
-She was different.
-No.

32:59.061 --> 33:01.062
I made her.

33:01.313 --> 33:02.480
I sent her back.

33:02.648 --> 33:04.482
-She's different.
-She's not different.

33:04.650 --> 33:07.109
There's physical damage to her chip...

33:07.277 --> 33:09.528
-...which means she can be repaired--
-John.

33:12.074 --> 33:13.324
I need her.

33:15.702 --> 33:17.411
She saved my life.

33:19.915 --> 33:21.540
She saves my life.

33:42.979 --> 33:45.147
I know what you saw today.

33:47.567 --> 33:52.488
I know what you did,
and I'm so proud of you.

33:54.700 --> 33:56.951
Maybe you could fix her.

33:58.120 --> 33:59.537
I know you wanna try...

34:02.958 --> 34:05.292
...but I can't let you. I just-- I can't.

34:13.385 --> 34:14.802
So burn her.

34:16.847 --> 34:19.014
Let's get the hell out of here.

34:41.788 --> 34:44.165
What she said back there...

34:45.500 --> 34:48.836
...everything she said was a trick.
You know that, right?

34:51.757 --> 34:53.382
They don't feel anything.

34:54.593 --> 34:57.178
They don't have feelings.

35:01.224 --> 35:03.350
They don't know love.

35:05.812 --> 35:07.605
I know that, Mom.

35:15.489 --> 35:18.449
Yeah, I saw her do this with the last one.

35:18.909 --> 35:21.035
DEREK:
Only way to be sure.

35:21.495 --> 35:23.370
Especially this one.

35:24.873 --> 35:26.749
John, chip.

36:08.291 --> 36:09.667
Flare. Where is it?

36:10.335 --> 36:12.628
-Sarah?
-Yeah.

36:29.062 --> 36:30.187
I'm sorry.

36:33.149 --> 36:34.316
DEREK:
John.

36:35.026 --> 36:36.360
John. Don't do this.

36:36.528 --> 36:39.071
-John, don't do this.
-Back off. John, she'll kill you.

36:39.239 --> 36:41.490
There's only one way to find out.

36:58.633 --> 37:00.092
Are you here to kill me, John?

37:02.596 --> 37:04.555
Are you here to kill me?

37:07.642 --> 37:08.893
No.

37:20.447 --> 37:21.530
Promise?

37:54.606 --> 37:56.065
Promise.

39:05.301 --> 39:06.885
I'll never lead you to her.

39:07.595 --> 39:11.390
If that's why you left me alive,
you might as well kill me right now.

39:11.558 --> 39:13.934
I'll never do the devil's work.

39:15.437 --> 39:17.396
We'll see.

39:27.282 --> 39:30.075
Thank you for joining me tonight.
I'm pleased to announce...

39:30.243 --> 39:31.910
...the formation of a new division.

39:32.078 --> 39:35.539
It'll cross disciplines,
draw from many areas of expertise...

39:35.707 --> 39:38.375
...and require the highest level of work
from your groups.

39:38.543 --> 39:40.961
Each of our groups?
How's that? Won't you be hiring?

39:41.129 --> 39:44.381
I'll take team members
from each division and create a new team.

39:44.549 --> 39:45.883
TUCK:
With all due respect...

39:46.217 --> 39:49.470
...and I can only speak on behalf
of the Al Division when I tell you...

39:49.637 --> 39:52.973
-...that I haven't a man to spare.
-Your division will be hard hit.

39:53.475 --> 39:57.352
The list of new team members will be on
your desks after you leave this meeting.

39:57.604 --> 40:01.774
The name of the new group is Babylon.
It's from the Bible.

40:02.150 --> 40:04.401
And what does Babylon do?

40:04.569 --> 40:07.071
I mean, besides steal our team members.

40:07.238 --> 40:11.450
Mr. Tuck, it's going to change the world.

40:20.335 --> 40:21.418
I got what I could.

40:21.878 --> 40:24.755
Some smoke and water damage,
but you don't have to start over.

40:25.507 --> 40:27.800
Wouldn't be the first time.

40:30.386 --> 40:32.971
-Thanks.
-There's one too many.

40:34.099 --> 40:36.767
Charlie took off. Said to say bye.

40:36.935 --> 40:38.936
I guess he really does have a wife.

40:49.197 --> 40:51.198
Have you seen John?

40:51.783 --> 40:53.492
I think he's using the shower.

40:56.162 --> 40:58.622
Do you believe in the Resurrection?

41:00.542 --> 41:01.542
What?

41:01.709 --> 41:05.170
The story of Jesus Christ.
The Resurrection.

41:05.338 --> 41:06.880
Do you believe in it?

41:07.048 --> 41:09.049
Would you, if you'd seen what I've seen?

41:09.217 --> 41:11.051
Faith isn't part of my programming.

41:11.219 --> 41:14.138
Yeah, well, I'm not sure
it's part of mine either.

41:16.850 --> 41:18.308
Don't let him do that again.

41:19.936 --> 41:24.148
If I ever go bad again,
don't let him bring me back.

41:31.823 --> 41:33.407
JOHN:
Yeah.

41:34.450 --> 41:37.703
I made you a sandwich
and brought you some clothes.

41:37.871 --> 41:39.788
I'll be out soon.

41:48.464 --> 41:52.050
John, I need you to know
everything that happened today...

41:52.260 --> 41:54.428
...everything we did...

41:56.181 --> 41:58.015
...it was all--

41:59.934 --> 42:02.561
It just happened the way it did...

42:02.979 --> 42:05.898
...and there's nothing we can do
to change it.

42:07.984 --> 42:10.068
And whatever happened, we're alive.

42:10.236 --> 42:12.446
Okay? We're alive.

42:14.991 --> 42:17.951
I know you need more from me today...

42:19.037 --> 42:21.371
...but it's gonna have to be enough.

42:25.418 --> 42:27.461
Can you hear me?

42:28.504 --> 42:30.297
Are you listening?

42:31.466 --> 42:33.383
JOHN:
Yeah, I'm listening.

42:38.223 --> 42:40.140
Happy birthday.

42:47.482 --> 42:51.276
Well, that was something, wasn't it?
Wonder what she's got planned.

42:51.444 --> 42:53.654
Who knows what goes on
in that brain of hers.

42:53.821 --> 42:56.907
I don't understand what the hell
she's talking about half the time.

42:57.075 --> 43:00.035
Zen koans and Bible quotes.

43:00.203 --> 43:01.495
It's all a bunch of bull.

43:01.663 --> 43:03.830
Our options have tripled
since she took over...

43:03.998 --> 43:06.333
...so I wouldn't bite the hand
if I were you.

43:06.501 --> 43:08.168
Well, that's easy for you to say.

43:08.336 --> 43:12.965
She's not cannibalizing your division
for some top-secret Torah study.

43:13.132 --> 43:15.008
Okay.

43:19.472 --> 43:22.516
God, that bitch pisses me off.

43:40.493 --> 43:43.662
Sorry I piss you off, Mr. Tuck.

43:55.842 --> 43:58.051
The feeling's mutual.
